First, we will prove two following lemmas:

\textbf{Lemma 1.}

Let $ABC$ be the acute and non-isosceles triangle. The points $M,N$ are the feets of perpendicular line from $A$ to the exterior angle bisector $B,C$ of triangle $ABC$. Let $P$ be the tangent point of line $BC$ and the excircle $(I)$ with respect to $BC$, $AQ$ is the altitudes of triangle $ABC$. Then $MNPQ$ is the isosceles trapezoid and $P$ is the orthocenter of triangle $MNI$.
